						               													<description>Berlin 1928: In the Babelsberg dream factory, the actress Zarah Leandros is on the verge of her breakthrough with her leading role in &amp;quot;The Red Angel&amp;quot;. But then the glamorous film diva mysteriously dies in the Berlin nightclub &amp;quot;Kakadu&amp;quot;. Has someone from her inner circle brought her career to an abrupt end? The spiritualist Prof. Magnusson wants to contact Zarah's spirit in the afterlife in a s&amp;eacute;ance and find out what really happened. The Professor comes into play as a voice on the CD (or as an mp3 link).&amp;#10;-from the publisher-&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the start of the game, each player receives an individual booklet for their role. The game is played over 3 rounds. Each round, the players have to share information from their booklet and additional hints they receive. Before the final discussion after round 3, one person learns that he is the murderer. After each one's summation, a ballot is taking place. If the murderer gets the most votes, he loses. Otherwise he wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
